1208
01:04:15,160 --> 01:04:17,000
It's a racing clown.

1209
01:04:17,040 --> 01:04:19,600
Can we just get on with it?
It's very hot in here.

1210
01:04:19,640 --> 01:04:21,280
Going with your window
down or up? Lot of stones.

1211
01:04:21,320 --> 01:04:22,560
Down?

1212
01:04:22,600 --> 01:04:24,400
It's a small risk
from being hit by a stone.

1213
01:04:24,440 --> 01:04:26,880
It's a large risk of
dying from suffocation.

1214
01:04:26,920 --> 01:04:29,360
Right. Anything else
we wanna say to him?

1215
01:04:29,400 --> 01:04:30,880
Yes. "Go."

1216
01:04:30,920 --> 01:04:32,360
Just take some time
and prepare mentally,

1217
01:04:32,400 --> 01:04:34,240
and really think about this.

1218
01:04:34,280 --> 01:04:36,160
-Have you visualised
the course?
-No.

1219
01:04:36,200 --> 01:04:38,680
RICHARD: OK.

1220
01:04:38,720 --> 01:04:40,960
JEREMY: He looks quite cross.
RICHARD: He does, yeah.

1221
01:04:41,000 --> 01:04:43,000
-Three, two, one, go!
-There you go.

1222
01:04:43,040 --> 01:04:44,480
Push.

1223
01:04:47,120 --> 01:04:48,520
Oh ,God, I can't...

1224
01:04:48,560 --> 01:04:51,360
I can't see round
right-hand bends because
of my sauna.

1225
01:04:54,680 --> 01:04:56,560
Whoa!

1226
01:04:56,600 --> 01:04:59,920
Massive hole there.

1227
01:04:59,960 --> 01:05:01,640
I've just realised that
I've only been comfortable

1228
01:05:01,680 --> 01:05:04,040
for 20 minutes
of this entire trip.

1229
01:05:04,080 --> 01:05:07,040
My car's been too hot,
my suit's too hot,

1230
01:05:07,080 --> 01:05:08,840
now the road's too rough.

1231
01:05:15,920 --> 01:05:18,720
Bit of squirrelling there
from the broken traction
control.

1232
01:05:24,320 --> 01:05:26,160
The finish line!

1233
01:05:26,200 --> 01:05:27,280
I've done it!

1234
01:05:31,080 --> 01:05:34,480
JEREMY: Next, it was my turn.

1235
01:05:34,520 --> 01:05:39,320
Right, I'm attaching the
wobbly-headed symbol
of Capitalism here,

1236
01:05:39,360 --> 01:05:41,880
to bring me good fortune
on this perilous test.

1237
01:05:43,240 --> 01:05:45,000
-If you're ready.
-Yes.

1238
01:05:45,040 --> 01:05:47,960
Five, four, three...
(LAUGHS)

1239
01:05:49,160 --> 01:05:51,160
...two, one.

1240
01:05:51,200 --> 01:05:52,880
Go!

1241
01:06:00,600 --> 01:06:03,360
Now, I'm guessing James May
will have gone for caution.

1242
01:06:03,400 --> 01:06:05,120
I'm not going to.

1243
01:06:06,520 --> 01:06:08,440
Cos I'm going
for speed and power.

1244
01:06:10,000 --> 01:06:13,040
And then just trust
in the BMW build quality.

1245
01:06:16,320 --> 01:06:19,000
My wobbly-headed symbol
of Capitalism is wilting.

1246
01:06:20,240 --> 01:06:22,240
It's not... Arrrgh!

1247
01:06:22,280 --> 01:06:24,880
Jesus, that was
a big tail slide there!

1248
01:06:25,960 --> 01:06:27,520
Oh, yeah.

1249
01:06:28,920 --> 01:06:31,600
Stick it in here. Oh, yes.

1250
01:06:34,600 --> 01:06:36,520
-(RATTLING)
-Oh, what's happened?

1251
01:06:40,920 --> 01:06:42,840
(RATTLING AND CLANKING)

1252
01:06:49,720 --> 01:06:51,240
Yeah.

1253
01:06:52,960 --> 01:06:54,720
-You overdid it, didn't you?
-Yeah.

1254
01:06:54,760 --> 01:06:57,240
JAMES: So I've won that.

1255
01:06:57,280 --> 01:06:59,280
Well, we don't know.
We haven't got your time yet.

1256
01:06:59,320 --> 01:07:03,400
You said - your words: "Test
of durability and is against
the clock."

1257
01:07:03,440 --> 01:07:05,440
Your car is broken.

1258
01:07:05,480 --> 01:07:08,920
-It's not broken,
a tyre's come off.
-It's broken.

1259
01:07:08,960 --> 01:07:10,800
RICHARD:
Down at the start line,

1260
01:07:10,840 --> 01:07:12,720
I was waiting
for the signal to go.

1261
01:07:14,680 --> 01:07:17,240
Hm. Little cubby hole.

1262
01:07:17,280 --> 01:07:19,000
JEREMY: Richard Hammond.

1263
01:07:20,160 --> 01:07:22,800
Hello, yes.

1264
01:07:22,840 --> 01:07:25,240
JEREMY: Three, two, one, go!
-Oh, come on, I'm not...

1265
01:07:25,280 --> 01:07:27,080
Right, OK, here I go.

1266
01:07:27,120 --> 01:07:28,680
(ENGINE REVS)

1267
01:07:28,720 --> 01:07:30,280
And we're off.

1268
01:07:30,320 --> 01:07:32,040
Oh, Christ! Oh.

1269
01:07:34,040 --> 01:07:35,520
I am limited on power.

1270
01:07:37,600 --> 01:07:39,520
Top speed: 39 miles an hour.

1271
01:07:39,560 --> 01:07:41,840
Ow, ow!

1272
01:07:41,880 --> 01:07:44,600
We're never gonna get an air
ambulance in here, are we?

1273
01:07:44,640 --> 01:07:46,560
Well, he might
have a very long winch.

1274
01:07:52,360 --> 01:07:53,840
Ohhh!

1275
01:07:53,880 --> 01:07:55,680
Big drops, I don't like that.
Ow!

1276
01:07:55,720 --> 01:07:58,080
Nervous of hill
climbs these days.

1277
01:08:01,440 --> 01:08:02,560
Agh, oh.

1278
01:08:03,640 --> 01:08:05,640
A line, use my line.

1279
01:08:05,680 --> 01:08:07,320
Ow.

1280
01:08:07,360 --> 01:08:08,480
Oh, my God!

1281
01:08:09,560 --> 01:08:11,080
Oh, dear!

1282
01:08:11,120 --> 01:08:12,800
Oh, God!

1283
01:08:20,880 --> 01:08:22,960
-Did anyone s...
-Was that...

1284
01:08:23,000 --> 01:08:26,760
-Did he just crash it?
-Was that a crash or did he
just disappear behind the...

1285
01:08:26,800 --> 01:08:28,720
He has, look,
he's gone off there.

1286
01:08:31,000 --> 01:08:32,400
Er...so there we are,

1287
01:08:32,440 --> 01:08:36,880
I'm afraid that
Richard Hammond's luck
has finally run out.

1288
01:08:36,920 --> 01:08:39,720
And it's with deep regret,
and great sadness,

1289
01:08:39,760 --> 01:08:43,600
that James and I
must now announce
the untimely demise of...

1290
01:08:43,640 --> 01:08:45,560
RICHARD: I'm all right.

1291
01:08:47,360 --> 01:08:49,360
-Not again.
-How's he do it?

1292
01:08:49,400 --> 01:08:51,400
I don't know.

1293
01:08:51,440 --> 01:08:53,040
Well, on that terrible
disappointment,

1294
01:08:53,080 --> 01:08:54,760
back to the tent.

1295
01:08:54,800 --> 01:08:57,760
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

1296
01:08:57,800 --> 01:09:02,600
-Look at my face.
-I'm OK. I'm OK.

1297
01:09:02,640 --> 01:09:04,040
JEREMY: Smug face.
-I'm fine.

1298
01:09:05,560 --> 01:09:07,440
-Don't worry.
-Smug.

1299
01:09:08,680 --> 01:09:11,080
Smug because I won that.

1300
01:09:11,120 --> 01:09:13,800
-No, you didn't.
-I did, I was the fastest.

1301
01:09:13,840 --> 01:09:18,560
And it was supposed to be a
test of fun and you moaned
the entire way up the hill.

1302
01:09:18,600 --> 01:09:22,160
It was a test of durability.
You had to change a wheel
and where's the fun in that?

1303
01:09:22,200 --> 01:09:24,920
Well, I wasn't the idiot that
put a sauna in my car.

1304
01:09:24,960 --> 01:09:26,360
What's wrong with a sauna?

1305
01:09:26,400 --> 01:09:28,800
Because in every hotel
that's got a sauna,

1306
01:09:28,840 --> 01:09:31,760
the corridors are
always full of wet idiots

1307
01:09:31,800 --> 01:09:33,640
with those slippers
that don't fit.

1308
01:09:33,680 --> 01:09:35,560
-Hello? Hello?
-What?

1309
01:09:35,600 --> 01:09:39,000
I did have quite a big crash
at the end there. I thought--

1310
01:09:39,040 --> 01:09:40,800
There's nothing particularly
remarkable about that,
is there?

1311
01:09:40,840 --> 01:09:42,040
I mean, why would you...

1312
01:09:42,080 --> 01:09:44,000
The fact is,
the reason you crashed...

1313
01:09:44,040 --> 01:09:46,000
Well, obviously
you're incompetent.

1314
01:09:46,040 --> 01:09:51,680
But also because your
Cadillac broke down and
your Mercedes was too humid.

1315
01:09:51,720 --> 01:09:54,720
So that means
the winner is definitely,
of the whole thing,

1316
01:09:54,760 --> 01:09:57,440
the BMW 750i.

1317
01:09:57,520 --> 01:09:59,360
-What?
-Actually, no.

1318
01:09:59,400 --> 01:10:02,800
To be fair, the real winner
of the whole thing was
our brilliant idea

1319
01:10:02,840 --> 01:10:05,720
to sell second-hand limos
to the Chinese.

1320
01:10:05,760 --> 01:10:07,280
No, he's absolutely right
about that,

1321
01:10:07,320 --> 01:10:08,960
because it makes them happy

1322
01:10:09,000 --> 01:10:11,120
and it helps us with
our balance of payments.

1323
01:10:11,160 --> 01:10:13,160
-Everybody wins.
-It was a good idea.

1324
01:10:13,200 --> 01:10:15,200
-Yes.
-Except for one tiny detail.

1325
01:10:15,240 --> 01:10:20,280
You see, this programme
is shown in every single
country in the world.

1326
01:10:20,320 --> 01:10:21,800
Except one.

1327
01:10:22,880 --> 01:10:24,400
(LAUGHTER)

1328
01:10:24,440 --> 01:10:26,080
-Which one?
-China.

1329
01:10:26,120 --> 01:10:27,680
Ah.

1330
01:10:27,720 --> 01:10:31,080
So this entire show has been
a total waste of time.

1331
01:10:31,120 --> 01:10:35,200
It's an hour of your life
you'll never get back.

1332
01:10:35,240 --> 01:10:37,320
And on that terrible
disappointment,
it's time to end.

1333
01:10:37,360 --> 01:10:40,040
Next week, I'm happy to say,
we're back in the groove.

1334
01:10:40,080 --> 01:10:43,400
We're in Scotland and I get
an Alfa Romeo GTV6,
make me very happy.

1335
01:10:43,440 --> 01:10:45,320
See you then, take care.
Good night.

1336
